data.text:
Norman Lee Keen, 63, of Scottsville, KY died at 2:50 p.m. Thursday, March 27, 2014 at his residence. The Portland, TN native was an employee of Berry Plastics, Viet Nam U. S. Army veteran, member of Abounding Grace Ministries and Halfrey Dalton VFW Post 5712. He was a son of the late Henry Edward Keen and Edna Pauline Dunn Keen.

He is survived by his wife: Martha "Janie" Keen, Scottsville, KY;

2 daughters: Angela Michele Keen and Marcia Lea Keen-Hood and husband, Ron, all of Scottsville, KY;

His mother-in-law: Mildred Steenbergen, Scottsville, KY;

1 brother: Ricky Keen and wife, Donna, Portland, TN;

3 sisters: Cherri York, Dalton, GA; Patsy Holmes and husband, Larry, Portland, TN; Donna Mosley and husband, Steve, Hendersonville, TN;

2 grandchildren: Garrette Lee Alan Keen and Makelia Pauline Dalton;

1 step granddaughter: McKenna Grace Hood;

1 grand puppy: Gracie Keen;

1 brother-in-law: Jesse Steenbergen, Jr. and wife, Jeanetta, Scottsville, KY;

3 sisters-in-law: Patsy Shaw; Raydell Holman and husband, Billy; and Judy Herald and husband, Mike, all of Scottsville, KY;

Several nieces and nephews and

A special family friend: Fredia Keen.

He was preceded in death by 2 brothers: Joe Darryl Keen and Billy Gene Keen and 2 sisters: Shirley Ann Clubbs and Margaret Johnson and his father-in-law: Jesse Steenbergen.

Funeral services will be 2:00 p.m. Sunday at Goad Funeral Home with Bro. Johnny Carver, Bro. Elvis Farley and Bro. Joe Shockley officiating and burial in Allen County Memorial Gardens with military rites by Glasgow DAV Chapter 20. Visitation will be 11:00 a.m. to 9:00 p.m. Saturday and after 8:00 a.m. Sunday until funeral time at Goad Funeral Home.
